\q1
\v 15 The sun and moon will grow dark,  
\q2 and the stars will no longer shine.   
\q1
\v 16 The \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w* will roar from Zion  
\q2 and raise His voice from Jerusalem;  
\q2 heaven and earth will tremble.  
\q1 But the \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w* will be \w a|strong="H3068"\w* refuge for His people,  
\q2 \w a|strong="H3068"\w* stronghold for the people of Israel.   
\s1 Blessings for God’s People  
\b  
\q1
\v 17 Then you will know that I am the \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w* your God,  
\q2 who dwells in Zion, My holy mountain.  
\q1 Jerusalem will be holy,  
\q2 never again to be overrun by foreigners.   
\b  
\q1
\v 18 And in that day the mountains will drip with sweet wine,  
\q2 and the hills will flow with milk.  
\q1 All the streams of Judah will run with water,  
\q2 and \w a|strong="H3068"\w* spring will flow from the house of the \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w*  
\q2 to water the Valley of Acacias.\f + \fr 3:18 \ft Or Valley of Shittim\f*   
\q1
\v 19 Egypt will become desolate,  
\q2 and Edom \w a|strong="H3068"\w* desert wasteland,  
\q1 because of the violence done to the people of Judah,  
\q2 in whose land they shed innocent blood.   
\q1
\v 20 But Judah will be inhabited forever,  
\q2 and Jerusalem from generation to generation.   
\q1
\v 21 For I will avenge their blood,  
\q2 which I have not yet avenged.\f + \fr 3:21 \ft Or For I will pardon their bloodguilt, which I have not yet pardoned.\f*”  
\qr For the \w LORD|strong="H3068"\w* dwells in Zion.  